From 656af477c0d3c4a1b327fcde010da4b9f0489c64 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 27 Jun 2026 17:18:17 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 05/42] B2c.2: weave the REAL canvas texture (replace synthetic
 SBS input)

#625 Step B. Replaces the B2c.1 synthetic test-pattern input with the
real tagged canvas texture, so the woven 3D shows the page's own canvas
pixels.

GPU-thread path (design doc webxr-step-b-design.md s7, step 2):
- Viz MaybeWeaveSubstitute resolves the tagged canvas quad's
  ID3D11Texture2D on the GPU thread via a SCANOUT-free overlay
  representation, then drives the weave from the real canvas.
- New provider entry WeaveCanvas(device, canvas_tex, slice, src, window)
  replaces WeaveSynthetic: the input keyed-mutex SBS texture is now
  allocated on the Viz GPU-main D3D11 device X (== the canvas device)
  and the canvas sub-rect is CopySubresourceRegion'd into it before the
  unchanged Mojo weave RPC / woven import / fence-wait / substitute.

Key findings baked into the change:
- Device identity: content_shell's Graphite-Dawn runs the D3D11 backend
  (kSkiaGraphiteDawnUseD3D12 default-off) which shares ANGLE's D3D11
  device, so canvas SI, DComp and context_state_->GetD3D11Device() are
  one device -> the CopySubresourceRegion is same-device. The provider
  no longer owns a private device.
- A normal 2D canvas SI is DISPLAY_READ-only (no SCANOUT), so the manager
  ProduceOverlay SCANOUT gate would reject it. Added Win-only
  ProduceOverlayForWeave (SharedImageManager + SharedImageRepresentation-
  Factory) = ProduceOverlay minus the SCANOUT enforcement; it still
  yields the D3D overlay representation whose GetDCLayerOverlayImage
  exposes the canvas ID3D11Texture2D.
- Input texture format taken from the canvas desc so the copy is always
  format-legal; canvas desc/format logged once for the BGRA-vs-RGBA risk.

Status: code-complete + builds clean. Live Leia eyeball still PENDING --
content_shell does not produce compositor frames under the automation
harness (rAF stuck at 0; foreground/resize/screencast/focus-emulation all
fail to tick the compositor), the same wall the B2c.1 runtime -2 was
diagnosed around. The full pipe is proven live up to the bind this
session: B2a window-bound weave session + GPU provider registered. The
canvas-pixels-in-3D eyeball needs a genuinely interactive desktop launch.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
